The paper discusses a planning system that uses heuristic search algorithms and explores different planning domains. This makes it likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of numerical state variables and plan quality objective functions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also mentions critical path analysis and linear time algorithms, which are topics that fall under the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The use of data structures and algorithms to improve performance suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the design and architecture of the planning system, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
